Flask Web App Setup

This Flask-based web application allows users to upload CSV files, apply normalization techniques to data, and visualize results.

Features

1. File Upload Handling (/upload)

Accepts CSV file uploads.

Reads the CSV file using Pandas.

Extracts column names and passes them to an HTML template for selection.

2. Normalization (/normalize)

Applies various normalization techniques:

MinMax Scaling

Standard Scaling

Robust Scaling

MaxAbs Scaling

Quantile Transformation

Log Transformation

Square Root Transformation

Box-Cox Transformation

Yeo-Johnson Transformation

Saves the transformed data as a CSV file.

Allows users to download the normalized file.

3. Visualization (/visualize)

Generates histograms for a selected column.

Converts the plot to a Base64-encoded image.

Renders the histogram in an HTML template.

4. Ensures Safe File Storage

Stores uploaded files in an uploads/ folder.

Automatically creates the folder if it is missing.
